					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10603274#post-4180194</guid>
				<title>How to Summon a Lemon - JamCon 2: Day 1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10603274/scp-4942#post-4180194</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 10 Mar 2019 19:12:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>stormbreath</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3075960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Originally, the demon at the end was a literal shaggy dog, but after seeing everybody take the prompt literally, I decided to remove that.</p> <p>The real shaggy dog of this SCP is the ritual itself, rather than the SCP file: while the file takes on the role a little, the ritual is incredibly specific and complex for nothing more than a common imp.</p> <p>Thanks to Othello, AthosNetwork and not_a_seagull for looking this over.</p> 
				 	]]>
